He went to Crawfords too. Yes. And he - he left there - never said anybody, just left and he had a job in Hatton Garden on the lifts. On the lifts in Hatton Garden. Tramway section of it like, And nobody knew -
 he just went and got it you know 'cos remember me father wasn't too pleased about it you know. He didn't like anybody working for the corporation when he was there. And - anyway he didn't stick that job for long. The next thing we knew he was missing lik
e - for a day or two. He'd jumped a ship - the landing stage thing. I think it was the boat - and he'd gone to America like and of course and of course it was two or three days after when we got to know.
